wined developments within the 'long duree' of the twentieth century and into the twenty-first. Beyond the Essay Film seeks to not only acknowledge the influential predecessors of this - in the view of many critics - most interesting type of contemporary filmmaking - but also to speculate about its possible transformation as we move forward into the uncharted waters of the twenty-first - digital -century. Focusing on three specific axes that underpin and shape the articulation of the essay film as a specific cultural form - subjectivity, textuality and technology - this book explores how changes along and across these dimensions affect historical shifts within essay film practice and its relation to other types of cinema and neighbouring art forms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aDocumentary films. 4aContemporary Society. 4aFilm Theory. 4aFilm, Media and Communication. 4aHistory of Film. 4aPhilosophy. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aEssay film, documentary, subjectivity, film studies, cinema.1 aBellour, Raymond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElsaesser, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibson, Ross, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrant, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Adrian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMisek, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPesch, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRascaroli, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVassilieva, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVassilieva, Julia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabul